### P1-03 · Core web vitals agent [CHAT]

```
Create agents/web-vitals-agent.ts — the Phase 1 core agent.

This agent receives a Page config and returns vitals measurements.

Requirements:
- Launch Playwright with the standard config from .cursor/rules
- For each page, run Lighthouse programmatically (not CLI) 3 times
- Use lighthouse/core package, desktop config, settings from .cursor/rules
- Extract these metrics from each run: LCP, CLS, INP, FCP, TTFB, TBT, Speed Index,
  Lighthouse performance score
- Return the MEDIAN of 3 runs for each metric (not average — median is more stable)
- Also capture: which DOM element is the LCP element (Lighthouse exposes this)
- Store the raw Lighthouse JSON to disk at ./raw-reports/{run-id}/{page-slug}-{n}.json
- Implement the 5-minute hard timeout from .cursor/rules
- Use the Result<T> pattern — never throw
- Log structured output: { agent: 'web-vitals', page, status, duration_ms }

The function signature should be:
  runWebVitalsAgent(page: PageConfig, runId: string): Promise<Result<VitalsMeasurement>>
```

