### P1-04 · Regression detector [INLINE]

```
Open db/queries.ts and add a detectRegression function.

The function:
  detectRegression(current: VitalsMeasurement, baseline: BaselineStats): RegressionReport

Should:
- Compare each metric in current against the baseline median from last 7 days
- Apply the thresholds from config/thresholds.ts
- Return a RegressionReport with:
    { hasRegression: boolean, regressions: MetricRegression[], severity: Severity }
- Each MetricRegression should include:
    { metric, currentValue, baselineValue, deltaPct, deltaAbsolute, severity }
- Severity calculation: use the CRITICAL/HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW rules from .cursor/rules
- If the page has no baseline yet (first run), return hasRegression: false and
  log a warning — never alert on first run
```

