### P1-06 · Orchestrator v1 (Phase 1 only) [CHAT]

```
Create agents/orchestrator.ts — the Phase 1 version that runs web vitals only.

The orchestrator:
1. Accepts a trigger: { type: 'deploy'|'scheduled'|'manual', deploySha?: string }
2. Creates a run record in the database with a UUID run ID
3. Reads all pages from config/pages.ts
4. Runs the web vitals agent for ALL pages in PARALLEL using Promise.allSettled
   (never Promise.all — one failure must not kill the others)
5. For each result:
   - On success: run detectRegression, store measurement, send alert if needed
   - On failure: mark page as FAILED in run record, log error, continue
6. Updates the run record with final status and completion time
7. Prints a summary to stdout: X pages passed, Y pages failed, Z regressions found

Each page run has the 5-minute timeout from .cursor/rules.
The orchestrator itself has a 15-minute global timeout.

Also create .github/workflows/perf-test.yml that:
- Triggers on: push to main, and daily at 02:00 IST (UTC+5:30 = 20:30 UTC)
- Sets all env vars from GitHub Secrets
- Runs: npm run test:perf
- Posts a comment on the PR with the summary if triggered by push
```

