### P2-02 · Screenshot baseline capture [CHAT]

```
Create a one-time script scripts/capture-baselines.ts for capturing visual baselines.

This runs once to establish the initial screenshot baselines.

Requirements:
- For each page in config/pages.ts, capture a full-page screenshot
- Capture at both viewports: desktop (1440x900) and mobile (390x844)
- Wait for: networkidle + all images loaded (wait for img elements to have naturalWidth > 0)
- Also capture a 3-second scroll video to establish scroll baseline
- Save to: ./baselines/{page-slug}/{viewport}/baseline_{timestamp}.png
- Save scroll video to: ./baselines/{page-slug}/{viewport}/scroll_baseline.mp4
- Write a baselines/manifest.json tracking:
    { pageSlug, viewport, capturedAt, filePath, checksum }
- Print instructions at the end: "Baselines captured. Review screenshots in ./baselines/
  before running tests. Run npm run test:visual to compare against these."
- Never overwrite existing baselines silently — prompt the user to confirm with --force flag
```

