### P2-03 · SSIM flicker and jank detector [CHAT]

```
Create agents/visual-qa-agent.ts — Phase 2 visual quality agent.

This agent detects visual regressions: flicker, jank, and layout shift.

Requirements:

PART 1 — FLICKER DETECTION
- Record a 5-second video of the page loading using Playwright's recordVideo
- Extract frames at 10fps using ffmpeg (spawn as child process)
- Calculate SSIM between consecutive frames using the ssim package
- FLICKER = SSIM drops more than 0.15 between any two consecutive frames
- Return: { hasFlicker: boolean, flickerFrames: number[], worstDrop: number }

PART 2 — SCROLL JANK DETECTION
- Inject a JS script that measures frame timing during a programmatic scroll:
    Use requestAnimationFrame to count actual vs expected frames over 3 seconds
- Jank = more than 5% of frames dropped (frame took > 32ms = dropped on 30fps baseline)
- Return: { jankScore: number, droppedFramePct: number, hasJank: boolean }

PART 3 — LAYOUT SHIFT EVIDENCE
- Capture screenshots at 500ms, 1s, 2s, 3s after navigation
- Run pixelmatch between each consecutive pair
- Return: diff images saved to ./diffs/{run-id}/, diffPixelCount per pair
- Correlate with CLS score from web vitals agent (they should agree directionally)

Agent function signature:
  runVisualQAAgent(page: PageConfig, runId: string): Promise<Result<VisualQAResult>>

Flicker and jank findings should be included in the Slack alert if they exceed thresholds.
```

