## PHASE 3 — LLM Analysis + 3P Script Audit

---

### P3-01 · Third-party script audit agent [CHAT]

```
Create agents/script-audit-agent.ts — the 3P script inventory agent.

This agent uses the HAR (HTTP Archive) from a Playwright run to identify all third-party
scripts and their performance cost.

Requirements:
- Enable HAR recording in Playwright context: recordHar: { path: './har/{run-id}/{page}.har' }
- After page load, parse the HAR file
- For each resource:
    - Identify if third-party: domain != indiamart.com and != www.indiamart.com
    - Extract: url, domain, size (compressed + uncompressed), timing (blocked ms, dns ms, connect ms, send ms, wait ms, receive ms)
    - Classify script type: analytics | advertising | chat | cdn | social | unknown
    - Calculate render-blocking score: was it in <head> without async/defer?
- Return a ScriptInventory:
    { totalThirdPartySize_kb, totalBlockingTime_ms, scripts: Script[] }
    where each Script has: { url, domain, type, size_kb, blockingTime_ms, isRenderBlocking }
- Sort by blockingTime_ms descending — worst offenders first
- Flag as HIGH_RISK if: isRenderBlocking AND size_kb > 30
- Store inventory in script_inventory table (db/schema.sql)
- Include top 5 offenders in the Slack report
```

---

### P3-02 · LLM analysis agent [CHAT]

```
Create agents/analysis-agent.ts — the Claude-powered root cause analysis agent.

This is Phase 3's core intelligence layer.

Requirements:
- Import Anthropic SDK: import Anthropic from '@anthropic-ai/sdk'
- Use model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514' (as per .cursor/rules)
- The agent receives:
    - MetricDelta: before/after values for all metrics (from getDelta in db/queries.ts)
    - deploySha: string (to fetch git diff)
    - ScriptInventory: from script audit agent
    - NetworkSimResult: the 4-profile matrix

STEP 1 — Fetch git diff
- Run: git diff {previousSha}..{currentSha} --stat --diff-filter=AM -- '*.js' '*.ts' '*.json'
- Truncate to 4000 chars if longer (send summary not full diff)

STEP 2 — Build the analysis prompt
System prompt:
  "You are a senior web performance engineer. Analyze the following performance
   regression and provide a root cause analysis. Respond ONLY with valid JSON
   matching the schema exactly. No prose outside the JSON object."

User message (JSON structure):
  {
    "metric_delta": { ...before/after for each metric with % change },
    "git_diff_summary": "...",
    "third_party_changes": [ high risk scripts from ScriptInventory ],
    "network_degradation": { "lcp_4g_to_slow3g_ratio": X, "worst_profile": "..." }
  }

STEP 3 — Parse and validate response
- Validate with zod against RegressionAnalysis schema:
    { severity, summary, root_cause, affected_metrics, recommendation, confidence }
- On parse failure: retry once with the error message appended to the prompt
- On second failure: return a fallback Result with raw text

STEP 4 — Log everything
- Log: { inputTokens, outputTokens, latencyMs, model, runId, pageSlug }

Function signature:
  runAnalysisAgent(delta: MetricDelta, context: AnalysisContext): Promise<Result<RegressionAnalysis>>
```

