### U-02 · Add structured logging to any file [INLINE]

```
Refactor all console.log statements in this file to use structured logging.

Requirements:
- Import the logger from utils/logger.ts (create it if it doesn't exist)
- Logger should use winston with JSON transport in production, pretty-print in development
- Every log call must include: { agent, pageSlug, runId } as context
- Map log levels: debug → verbose operational info, info → key milestones,
  warn → non-fatal issues, error → failures with full error object
- Add timing logs: log at start and end of every agent function with duration_ms
- Never log: raw SQL queries, full HAR files, full Lighthouse JSON, or API keys
```

