### U-04 · Tune alert thresholds [CHAT]

```
I've collected 2 weeks of baseline data. Here are the p50/p75/p95 values
for our key pages: [PASTE DATA FROM GRAFANA OR DB QUERY]

Looking at this data, our current alert thresholds in config/thresholds.ts
may be too aggressive (too many false positives) or too loose (missing real regressions).

Recommend updated thresholds for each metric on each page based on the actual
variance in the data. A good threshold should:
- Catch genuine regressions (deploy-correlated drops > normal variance)
- Not alert on natural daily variance (time-of-day traffic patterns)
- Use different baselines for peak hours vs off-peak if the data shows > 15% variance

Output the updated thresholds as a TypeScript object ready to paste into config/thresholds.ts.
```

